text: The Black spiny-chest frog (Alsodes nodosus) is a frog. It lives in Chile.. ==Home== Scientists found this frog places with short woody plants near streams. Scientists saw this frog between 150 and 1900 meters above sea level. Scientists have seen this frog might inside some protected parks: Cerro La Campana National Park, Río Clarillo National Reserve, and Roblería del Cobre de Loncha National Reserve. ==Danger== Scientists from the IUCN and from the government of Chile say this frog is in a little danger of dying out. People change the places where the frog lives to make towns and cities, make farms, and get wood to build with. Fish and bigger frogs from other parts of the world might eat this frog. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Alsodes nodosus
